# CONTEXT.md is the living memory — read it, keep it current

`CONTEXT.md` (project root) is the single living context/memory for this project:
architecture, decisions, behaviors, data quirks, gotchas, endpoints, and current
state. It is the canonical hand-off between sessions.

## Always refer to it

- **At the start of every task, READ `CONTEXT.md` first** to load current state
  before searching code or making changes. Trust it, but verify against code when
  something looks stale.

## Always update it

- After **any** change or discovery, **update `CONTEXT.md` in the same session**:
  new features, fixes, decisions (and the reasoning), newly observed runtime
  behavior, NSE data quirks, added/changed endpoints, config knobs, gotchas.
- Keep the **"Findings & change log"** section at the bottom append-only and dated
  (IST), newest first.
- If you learn something that contradicts CONTEXT.md, correct it immediately.

Never let CONTEXT.md drift from reality. When in doubt, over-document here.
